# Walkthrough: FastAPI Celery Worker Service

This document summarizes the complete implementation of the dedicated FastAPI Celery worker service designed to run background tasks, schedules (via Celery Beat), and monitoring (via Flower) for the power tracker system, entirely decoupled from the Django (Laundry) application.

## Summary of Changes

### Project Configuration & Setup
- **[pyproject.toml](file:///C:/Users/Pro/Desktop/PROJECT/TEST/worker/pyproject.toml)**: Configured with `fastapi`, `celery`, `redis`, `flower`, `sqlalchemy`, `psycopg2-binary`, `python-dotenv`, `pytz`, and `requests`. Managed and synced via `uv`.
- **[.env](file:///C:/Users/Pro/Desktop/PROJECT/TEST/worker/.env)**: Contains local and remote environment parameters including database credentials (`DATABASE_URL`), SMTP authentication, and Evolution API credentials.
- **[.dockerignore](file:///C:/Users/Pro/Desktop/PROJECT/TEST/worker/.dockerignore)**: Excludes caches, the `.venv` directory, `.env` files, and IDE workspace configs from the build context.
- **[Dockerfile](file:///C:/Users/Pro/Desktop/PROJECT/TEST/worker/Dockerfile)**: Multi-stage slim image build based on `python:3.13-slim`. It uses `uv` for dependency resolution, compilation of byte-code, and compiles a slim production image.

### Application Logic & Architecture
- **[__init__.py](file:///C:/Users/Pro/Desktop/PROJECT/TEST/worker/worker/__init__.py)**: Standard Python package initializer.
- **[db.py](file:///C:/Users/Pro/Desktop/PROJECT/TEST/worker/worker/db.py)**: Establishes a connection pool using SQLAlchemy's `create_engine` with `pool_pre_ping=True` and a thread-safe `sessionmaker`.
- **[celery_app.py](file:///C:/Users/Pro/Desktop/PROJECT/TEST/worker/worker/celery_app.py)**: Configures Celery with Redis broker/backend and registers the daily-power-summary scheduler running at `00:01` daily in the `Africa/Lagos` timezone.
- **[tasks.py](file:///C:/Users/Pro/Desktop/PROJECT/TEST/worker/worker/tasks.py)**: Migrated all 7 original background tasks from Django (`myapp.tasks.*`). All Django ORM DB operations were fully converted to SQLAlchemy raw SQL queries to ensure the worker runs independently of the Django codebase. Mappings preserved for:
  - `myapp.tasks.send_email_async`
  - `myapp.tasks.add`
  - `myapp.tasks.send_test_email`
  - `myapp.tasks.send_test_email1`
  - `myapp.tasks.send_power_email`
  - `myapp.tasks.send_daily_power_updates`
  - `myapp.tasks.send_security_alert_email`
- **[main.py](file:///C:/Users/Pro/Desktop/PROJECT/TEST/worker/worker/main.py)**: Exposes the HTTP Gateway API endpoints:
  - `GET /api/test-email/` (GET) enqueues a test power email task.
  - `POST /power-tracker-gateway/` (POST) parses incoming hardware alerts, validates the node credentials, checks for SIM mismatch security alerts, saves the status in the database, and offloads processing tasks to Celery.

